Well I do love the Yamaha YXZ but with a family of 4 the 2 
Seats just doesn't cut it!

node.text:
Just stepped off the plane back in the OC after one of the coolest events I have ever been a part of @sigsauerhunting knocked it out of the park with the inaugural SIG SAUER HUNTING GAMES.  Not one detail overlooked, this will be on my yearly must list for years to come. 

Team's we're comprised of three people each from different walks of life, all with exceptional shooting skills. From sharpshooters to avid hunters this was bound to be a battle. Not only shooting but scaling land up to 9000 feet, 8-mile distance it was gonna be up to the finest. 

Therefore, my team and I were against some of the best shooting team's in the world. Points we're super tight at the end of the two-day event and it came down to splitting hairs for the finishing podium.

I would bet our team had some of the best Communication out of all the teams, our RSO @pats1512 did a great job keeping us on time as well as giving us small tips to improve our shots! 

As for @therichoutdoors  @mrdavidwise @pats1512 and myself what a blast we had as a team pushing to improve every shot for a strong 5th place. 

Again thank you @sigsauerhunting for this opportunity!
